Description: SPQR addresses the integration of heterogeneous datasets in the humanities- specifically data relating to classical antiquity- using a linked data approach and based on the recently published Europeana Data Model (EDM). Published data includes:* The Heidelberger Gesamtverzeichnis der griechischen Papyrusurkunden Aegyptens (HGV)- a collection of metadata records for 65-000 Greek papyri from Egypt.* Projet Volterra- a database of Roman legal texts- currently in the low tens of thousands but very much work in progress- stored in a series of themed tables in Microsoft Access.* The Inscriptions of Aphrodisias (InsAph)- a corpus of 2-000 ancient Greek inscriptions from the Roman city of Aphrodisias.RDF dumps and a SPARQL endpoint are available. At this time the project does not use resolvable URIs.
Sources: Web:http://spqr.cerch.kcl.ac.uk/ Name:King’s College London; Humboldt-Universität Berlin; University of Edinburgh Email:Absent
